com.cyc.baseclient.inference

Class DefaultResultSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.inference.AbstractResultSet
      • com.cyc.baseclient.inference.DefaultResultSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InferenceResultSet, AutoCloseable, ResultSet, Wrapper

    public final class DefaultResultSet
extends AbstractResultSet

    DefaultResultSet provides a class for easy access and manipulation of inference results. It tries to closely mimic the java.sql.ResultSet class. One difference between java.sql.ResultSet and DefaultResultSet is that DefaultResultSet is zero-based while java.sql.ResultSet is one-based. Example: 

     System.out.println("Starting");
 CycAccess access = null;
 try {
   access = CycAccessManager.getAccess();
   ELMt inferencePSC = CommonConstants.INFERENCE_PSC;
   String query = "(#$isa ?X #$Dog)";
   InferenceWorkerSynch worker = new DefaultInferenceWorkerSynch(query,
       inferencePSC, null, access, 500000);
   DefaultResultSet rs = worker.executeQuery();
   try {
     int indexOfX = rs.findColumn("?X");
     while (rs.next()) {
       CycObject curDog = rs.getCycObject(indexOfX);
       System.out.println("Got dog: " + curDog.cyclify());
     }
   } finally {
     rs.close();
   }
 } catch (Exception e) {
   e.printStackTrace();
 } finally {
   if (access != null) {
     access.close();
   }
 }
 System.out.println("Finished");
 System.out.flush();

      • isInferenceComplete

        public boolean isInferenceComplete()
        Returns whether the InferenceWorker associated with this DefaultResultSet object is finished working. Will return true if there is no InferenceWorker.
        Returns:
        true if the InferenceWorker associated with this DefaultResultSet or if the InferenceWorker is not set; false if the InferenceWorker associated with this DefaultResultSet might possibly produce more results.

      • close

        public void close()
        Releases this DefaultResultSet object's server side inference resources. Failure to close a result set may leave significant resources hanging around the server until the client CycClient object is closed.

        Calling the method close on a DefaultResultSet object that is already closed is a no-op.

        Specified by:
        close in interface InferenceResultSet
        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
        Specified by:
        close in interface ResultSet
        Overrides:
        close in class AbstractResultSet
        Throws:
        IOException - if a communication error occurs
        TimeOutException - if doesn't get a response from the server before an excessive amount of time has elapsed
        CycApiException - if an internal server error occurs

      • getCloseTimeout

        public long getCloseTimeout()
        Description copied from interface: InferenceResultSet
        Returns the timeout for the InferenceResultSet.close() method. By default, returns the timeout of the InferenceWorker which returned this object, or this class's own internal default (typically 10,000 milliseconds), whichever is greater. This value may be changed by calling InferenceResultSet.setCloseTimeout(Long).
        Returns:
        timeout in milliseconds

      • setCloseTimeout

        public void setCloseTimeout(Long timeoutMS)
        Description copied from interface: InferenceResultSet
        Set the timeout for the InferenceResultSet.close() method returned by InferenceResultSet.getCloseTimeout(). Specifying a non-null value here will, naturally, override the default value. Specifying a null value will clear the overridden value, and InferenceResultSet.getCloseTimeout() will return its usual default.
        Parameters:
        timeoutMS - timeout in milliseconds

        Returns, as an Object, the value at the current row and at the column identified by col which should be a CycVariableImpl in the original query. Returns null if no value is set for the current row and given column.
